  "text": "Embosser is a Braille printer used to print Braille on a special sheet of paper. Standard Braille printed document contains text of twenty five rows and each row contains forty cells and its physical dimension is approximately 11 inches by 11 inches. There is the standard for the dimension of Braille cell as printed on the Embosser [CITATION_1] , but in some countries it may slightly vary where they use cell of eight dots.",
